	   <tr><td colspan=2>So ya all know, Revenants in hate are VERY rarely pulled, it takes (on average) 7 hours to get to the revenant houses in hate, from the break to the first house about 7 hours, thats including having to kill a MOB stronger then the god innuurok or however it is spelled, damn maestro with his AE life tap is no joke, and rev houses are past him, there are about 5 random spawns earlier in that zone that CAN have revs, usualy do not but they can, and when ya finaly do get to the rev houses after long hard hours, most of the people in the raid leave cause all their armor is done since only revenants are left, the revs very rarely drop armor (go verant!) and then, in my personal experience tons of mages just LOVE to join the raid right after maestro dies, so ya go from bein the only mage there for 7 hours, then all the sudden there is 5 mages there and ya gotta share with all them, and basicly get screwed =), verant really needs to move about 3 of the 10 revenant houses near the port in spot in my oppinion...balance things out, i've been to hate 35sh times and made it to rev houses 5 times...that is rediculous, 30 trips to hate, where my armor drops, with virtualy no chance of even gettin armor<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
